{{Infobox protected area | name = Dalby Söderskog National Park | alt_name = Dalby Söderskogs nationalpark | iucn_category = II | photo = Dalby Söderskog nationalpark1.jpg | photo_width = 288 | photo_caption = | location = [[Skåne County]], [[Sweden]] | nearest_city = [[Lund]] | coords = {{coord|55|40|N|13|19|E|region:SE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | area_km2 = 0.36 | area_ref = <ref name="naturvårdsverket">{{cite web |title=Dalby Söderskog National Park |url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Dalby-Soderskog-National-Park/ |publisher=[[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]] |accessdate=2009-02-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110326165208/http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Dalby-Soderskog-National-Park/ |archivedate=2011-03-26 |df= }}</ref> | established = 1918<ref name="naturvårdsverket" /> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]] | website = }} {{Swedish National Parks}} '''Dalby Söderskog''' is a small [[national park]] in the province of [[Scania]] in southern [[Sweden]], situated in the [[Lund Municipality|municipality of Lund]], near [[Dalby, Lund Municipality|Dalby]]. It has an area of {{convert|0.36|km2|mi2|abbr=on}} and consists of broadleaf forest. It was established in 1918, when it was thought to be a unique remnant of primeval forest. In fact, the area has previously been used for [[pasture]]. The ground contains much [[limestone]] and [[chalk]], which makes the flora rich. In particular, there are many spring flowers. An earth bank of unknown origin, possibly the ruins of an ancient fort, surrounds parts of the park. The national park encompasses the southern part of [[Dalby hage]], while the northern parts ([[Dalby Norreskog]] and Hästhagen) form a nature reserve.
