{{Infobox book | name = Mottainai Grandma | image = Mottainai Grandma.jpg | website = http://mottainai.com/e/ | author = Mariko Shinju | country = [[Japan]] | orig_lang_code = ja | title_orig = もったいないばあさん | language = [[Japanese language|Japanese]] | publisher = [[Kodansha]] | release_date = 2004 }}
'''''Mottainai Grandma''''' is the first book from the "Mottainai Grandma" series written by Japanese author Mariko Shinju. The book was published in 2004 The Japanese word ''[[mottainai]]'' means "wasteful".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=14054262|title=Mottainai Grandma Reminds Japan, 'Don't Waste'|publisher=}}</ref>
On January 13, 2018, it was released in Hindi and English translation in [[New Delhi]], India, by the [[Japan International Cooperation Agency]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20180115/p2a/00m/0et/015000c|title=Waste-battling 'Mottainai Grandma' book gets Hindi, English launch in India|date=15 January 2018|publisher=|via=Mainichi Daily News}}</ref> An earlier Japanese-English bilingual edition (pictured) was published by [[Kodansha]] in November 2005.<!-- This date and publisher come from honto.jp. Not sure if the book itself would be a reasonable source for this information, though. -->
Shinju started having ideas about writing the book while trying to explain wastefulness to her child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.treehugger.com/culture/mottainai-reduce-reuse-recycle-gets-ethical-in-japan-and-beyond.html|title=Mottainai! "Reduce, Reuse, Recycle" Gets Ethical in Japan and Beyond|publisher=}}</ref>
