{{coord|43|42|26|N|39|46|27|E|scale:20000|display=title}} [[File:Orekhovsky waterfall.JPG|thumb]] The '''Orekhovsky''' (Ореховский) is a [[waterfall]] in the [[Sochi National Park]]. It takes its name from [[Orekhovka]], a settlement in the [[Khosta District]] of [[Sochi]]. It is located on the Bezumenka stream at its confluence with the [[Sochi River]]. Orekhovsky is the second highest waterfall in the city, with a height of 27.5&nbsp;meters.<ref name="kuban">{{cite web|url=http://www.kuban.aif.ru/culture/details/488075|title=Выпущена новая серия олимпийских марок "Сочи 2014" &#124; КУЛЬТУРА: События &#124; КУЛЬТУРА &#124; АиФ Краснодар|publisher=kuban.aif.ru|accessdate=2014-03-09}}</ref> In the early 20th century, it was known as ''Melnichny'' ("the miller's fall").<ref name="SochiExc">{{cite web|url=http://www.sochi.com/exc/?region=74&id=27|title=Экскурсии Сочи / Водопад Ореховский, ореховские водопады в сочи|publisher=sochi.com|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref> Nearby is a grove of [[walnut]]s and [[rhododendron]].
