{{Infobox person | name = Vaibhav Kaul | native_name = {{lang-ks|वैभव कौल, ویبهو کول}} | birth_date = 1991 | nationality = Indian | alma_mater = [[University of Oxford]] | occupation = [[Geographer]] | known_for = [[Mountain research]], [[visual art]] }}
'''Vaibhav Kaul''' (born 1991) is a Himalayan photographer, painter, geographer and environmental scholar.<ref name="Deccan Herald">{{cite news|title=A visual ode to the mighty Himalayas|newspaper=Deccan Herald|date= 29 September 2015|accessdate=20 October 2015|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/503374/a-visual-ode-mighty-himalayas.html}}</ref><ref name="Indian Express">{{cite news|title=Echoes from the Mountains|newspaper=The Indian Express|date= 24 June 2016|accessdate=24 June 2016|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/lifestyle/art-and-culture/delhi-exhibition-ihc-mountains-vaibhav-kaul-talk-2872077/}}</ref><ref name="Hindu 2013">{{cite news|title=Framing the Himalayan landscape|newspaper=The Hindu|date=3 May 2013|accessdate=20 July 2014|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-newdelhi/framing-the-himalayan-landscape/article4678895.ece}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Arresting charm of snow-clad mountains|newspaper=Deccan Herald|date=15 July 2014|accessdate=20 July 2014|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/419712/arresting-charm-snow-clad-mountains.html}}</ref><ref name="Yale">{{cite web| url=http://e360.yale.edu/feature/unnatural_disaster_how_global_warming_helped_cause_indias_catastrophic_flood/2888/| title= Unnatural Disaster: How Global Warming Helped Cause India’s Catastrophic Flood | publisher= Yale Environment 360 | accessdate= 29 June 2015}}</ref><ref name="Hindu 2015">{{cite news|title=Calling out to the mountains|newspaper=The Hindu|date= 27 September 2015|accessdate=20 October 2015|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/calling-out-to-the-mountains/article7693382.ece}}</ref> He is a [[Fellow]] of the [[Royal Geographical Society]] and the [[Royal Asiatic Society]], an alumnus of the [[Environmental Change Institute]] at the [[University of Oxford]], and a researcher at the [[University of Sheffield]].<ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.sheffield.ac.uk/geography/phd/pg/vaibhav_kaul| title= Researcher profile: Vaibhav Kaul| publisher= The University of Sheffield | accessdate= 22 October 2014}}</ref><ref name="Kaul2014">{{cite journal |last1=Kaul |first1=V. |last2=Thornton |first2=T.F. |year=2014 |title=Resilience and adaptation to extremes in a changing Himalayan environment |journal=Regional Environmental Change |volume=14 |issue =2 |pages=683–698 |doi=10.1007/s10113-013-0526-3}}</ref><ref name="Yale"/><ref name="Deccan Herald"/> He has investigated [[Socio-ecological system|socio-environmental change]] in the high-mountain regions of [[Lahaul and Spiti district|Lahaul]], [[Garhwal division|Garhwal]], [[Kumaon division|Kumaon]] and [[Sikkim]] in India.<ref name="Kaul2014"/><ref name="Deccan Herald"/><ref>{{cite web| url= http://blogs.agu.org/landslideblog/2013/10/29/kedarnath-photo-2/| title= Kedarnath debris flow disaster| publisher= American Geophysical Union Blogosphere | accessdate= 22 July 2014}}</ref><ref name="Yale"/><ref>{{cite web| url= http://www.earthisland.org/journal/index.php/elist/eListRead/high_up_in_the_himalayas_villagers_live_under_the_shadow_of_an_unpredictabl/| title= High up in the Himalayas, villagers live under the shadow of an unpredictable lake| publisher= Earth Island Journal | accessdate= 22 December 2014}}</ref><ref name="Kak">{{cite news|title=Through the Doorways|newspaper=The Indian Express|date= 18 May 2017|accessdate=18 May 2017|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/lifestyle/books/through-the-doorways-4661106/}}</ref><ref name="Kak2">{{cite news|title=Picture Gallery: Kumaon: In the Shadow of the Devi |newspaper=Hindustan Times|date= 7 June 2017|accessdate=29 June 2017|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/books/picture-gallery-kumaon-in-the-shadow-of-the-devi-by-manju-kak/story-vVgoIrASnKAZpYNVN2j9mJ.html}}</ref><ref name="Kak3">{{cite news|title=Exploring Kumaon through its art, craftsmanship and woodwork (Book Review)|newspaper=Business Standard|date= 23 June 2017|accessdate=29 June 2017|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/exploring-kumaon-through-its-art-craftsmanship-and-woodwork-book-review-117062300195_1.html}}</ref> His [[landscape painting|landscape art]], [[Geophotography|visual geomorphology]] and [[Visual anthropology|visual ethnography]] works have been exhibited and published in South Asia, Europe and North America.<ref name="Indian Express"/><ref>{{cite web| url= http://blogs.agu.org/landslideblog/2013/10/26/kedarnath-photo/| title= A remarkable photo of Kedarnath after the debris flow disaster| publisher= American Geophysical Union Blogosphere | accessdate= 22 July 2014}}</ref><ref name="Deccan Herald"/><ref>{{cite news|title=The Himalayan Saga|newspaper=The Asian Age|date=13 July 2014|accessdate=20 July 2014|url=http://www.asianage.com/arts/himalayan-saga-071}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url= http://www.indiahabitat.org/calendar/May2013/exhibition.htm| title= Calendar of Events| publisher= India Habitat Centre | accessdate= 21 July 2014}}</ref><ref name="Hindu 2015"/><ref name="Yale"/><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.ruralindiaonline.org/articles/photostorm/ | title= Photostorm: Women and their many worlds| publisher= PARI | accessdate= 22 June 2015}}</ref><ref name="The Sunday Guardian">{{cite news|title=Picture essay: Moving with the glaciers |newspaper=The Sunday Guardian|date= 9 July 2016|accessdate=20 February 2017|url=http://www.sundayguardianlive.com/album/moving-glaciers}}</ref><ref name="London Photo Festival 1">{{cite news|title=We announce the top 20 exhibition photographs in our landscape photography contest in London|newspaper=London Photo Festival Blog|date= 10 September 2016|accessdate=10 October 2016|url=https://londonphotofestival.wordpress.com/2016/09/10/we-announce-the-top-20-exhibition-photographs-in-our-landscape-photocontest-photography-london/}}</ref><ref name="London Photo Festival 2">{{cite news|title=We announce the honourable mentions in our landscape photography contest in London|newspaper=London Photo Festival Blog|date= 10 September 2016|accessdate=10 October 2016|url=https://londonphotofestival.wordpress.com/2016/09/10/we-announce-the-honourable-mentions-in-our-landscape-photocontest-photography-london/}}</ref> He collaborated with the film director Ross Harrison to make ''Facing the Mountain'', a 2016 documentary about faith, resilience and change in the [[Himalayas]].<ref name="Facing the Mountain 1">{{cite web| url=http://www.geog.ox.ac.uk/news/articles/161116-facingthemountain.html| title= 90 years in the Himalayas: from ground-breaking surveys to documentary films | publisher= School of Geography and the Environment, University of Oxford | accessdate= 29 November 2016}}</ref><ref name="Facing the Mountain 2">{{cite web| url=https://www.sheffield.ac.uk/geography/news/facing-the-mountain-1.665562| title=Department hosts documentary film premiere| publisher= Department of Geography, University of Sheffield | accessdate=15 December 2016}}</ref><ref name="Facing the Mountain 3">{{cite web| url=http://trentofestival.it/edizione-2017/programma/film/facing-the-mountain/| title=Selezione Ufficiale: Facing the Mountain di Ross Harrison e Vaibhav Kaul (India/Regno Unito, 2016) | publisher=Trento Film Festival 2017 | accessdate=29 April 2017}}</ref><ref name="Facing the Mountain 4">{{cite web| url= http://www.qeh.ox.ac.uk/node/22234| title=Facing the Mountain | publisher= Oxford Department of International Development | accessdate=15 December 2016}}</ref><ref name="Facing the Mountain 5">{{cite web| url= https://vimff.org/films/facing-the-mountain/| title=Official Selection: Facing the Mountain (India, 2016) | publisher= Vancouver International Mountain Film Festival 2017 | accessdate=15 February 2017}}</ref><ref name="Facing the Mountain 7">{{cite web| url=http://www.iaac.us/nyiff2017/schedule.htm| title=Festival Schedule: Facing the Mountain (Harrison and Kaul, 2016) | publisher=New York Indian Film Festival 2017 | accessdate=29 April 2017}}</ref><ref name="Facing the Mountain 6">{{cite web| url=http://bufvc.ac.uk/events/learningonscreen/nominations-announced-2017-awards| title=Learning on Screen Awards 2017 Nomination: Facing the Mountain | publisher= British Universities Film and Video Council | accessdate=15 March 2017}}</ref> He appeared in ''An Awakening'', a poetic Anglo-Himalayan [[art film]] that he created with the cinematographer John Seddon as part of a 2017 video [[autoethnography]] experiment.<ref name="An Awakening 1">{{cite web| url= http://www.mountainfest.co.uk/film/detail/an-awakening| title=Official Selection: An Awakening (UK, 2017) | publisher= Kendal Mountain Festival 2017 | accessdate=19 November 2017}}</ref>
